{"title_page": "2020 New Zealand euthanasia referendum", "text_new": "{{Use New Zealand English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox referendum\n| name        = 2020 New Zealand euthanasia referendum\n| title       = ''Do you support the [[End of Life Choice Act 2019]] coming into force?''\n| date        = 19 September 2020\n| yes         = \n| no          = \n| total       = \n| turnout     = \n}}\n{{Politics of New Zealand}}\n\nThe '''New Zealand euthanasia referendum''' will be a binding [[referendums in New Zealand|referendum]],<ref name=\"Guardian vote\"/> held alongside the [[2020 New Zealand general election|19 September 2020 general election]] on the question of whether to legalise [[voluntary euthanasia]] for those with a terminal illness and less than six months left to live if approved by two doctors.<ref name=\"Guardian vote\"/><ref name=\"NZH pass\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12284982|title=Euthanasia bill passes final vote, goes to referendum|date=13 November 2019|accessdate=14 November 2019|work=The New Zealand Herald}}</ref> New Zealand is the first country to put euthanasia legalisation to a referendum.<ref name=\"Guardian vote\">{{cite news|url=https://theguardian.com/society/2019/nov/13/new-zealand-to-vote-in-referendum-on-euthanasia-cannabis|title=New Zealand to vote in referendum on euthanasia|first=Charlotte|last=Graham-McLay|date=13 November 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref> If over half of respondents vote in support of the legislation, it will become law exactly one year after the final vote count is announced.<ref name=\"referendum info\"/>\nA [[2020 New Zealand cannabis referendum|referendum on personal cannabis consumption]] will be held at the same time. The results of these referendums are expected to be released on 2 October.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/politics/118983011/jacinda-ardern-announces-2020-election-will-be-held-on-september-19 |title=Jacinda Ardern announces 2020 election will be held on September 19 |first1=Luke |last1=Malpass |first2=Henry |last2=Cooke |work=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]] |date=28 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n{{main|Euthanasia in New Zealand|End of Life Choice Act 2019}}\n\nEuthanasia is currently illegal in New Zealand, and it is illegal to \"aid and abet suicide\" under Section 179 of the [[New Zealand Crimes Act 1961]].\n\nTwo attempts to allow for legal euthanasia in New Zealand have failed to get through Parliament. A 1995 Death with Dignity Bill failed by 61 votes against and 29 supporting, and a 2003 Death with Dignity Bill failed in its first reading by 60 votes opposing to 58 supporting.<ref>{{cite web |title=Assisted dying: New Zealand - New Zealand Parliament |url=https://www.parliament.nz/en/pb/library-research-papers/research-papers/assisted-dying-new-zealand/ |website=www.parliament.nz |accessdate=14 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\n[[ACT New Zealand|ACT]] MP [[David Seymour (New Zealand politician)|David Seymour]] entered the [[End of Life Choice Bill]] to the [[private member's bill]] ballot in October 2015.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seymour|first1=David |title=Seymour lodges assisted dying Bill|url=http://www.act.org.nz/posts/seymour-lodges-assisted-dying-bill|website=ACT.org.nz|accessdate=4 December 2015}}</ref> The bill passed its first reading 76\u201344 in December 2017, its second reading 70\u201350 in June 2019,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12244205|title=Euthanasia bill passes second reading|work=New Zealand Herald|accessdate=26 June 2019|date=26 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/political/393021/euthanasia-bill-passes-second-reading-in-parliament|accessdate=26 June 2019|date=26 June 2019|work=Radio New Zealand|title=Euthanasia bill passes second reading in Parliament}}</ref> and its third reading 69\u201351 in November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/politics/beehive-live/117384206/mps-vote-on-final-reading-of-end-of-life-choice-bill|title=MPs vote in favour of End of Life Choice Bill at final reading|website=Stuff.co.nz|first=Henry|last=Cooke|date=13 November 2019|access-date=13 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Referendum ==\nThe public will get to vote on whether to legalise voluntary euthanasia as [[New Zealand First]] threatened to vote down the legislation if it did not go to a referendum, while the Green party demanded more safeguards to ensure that only terminally ill patients would be covered, and could not be coerced.<ref name=\"NZH pass\"/> The decision to go to a referendum passed 69\u201351.<ref name=\"Stuff pass\">{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/politics/117395669/euthanasia-bill-passes-6951-sending-the-final-decision-to-a-referendum|title=Euthanasia bill passes 69-51, sending the final decision to a referendum|first=Henry|last=Cooke|work=Stuff.co.nz|date=13 November 2019|access-date=14 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Referendum question==\nThe question asked of voters will be:<ref name=\"referendum info\">{{cite web|url=https://www.referendum.govt.nz/endoflifechoice/index.html|title=Referendum on the End of Life Choice Act 2019|website=referendum.govt.nz|publisher=New Zealand Government|accessdate=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n:''Do you support the End of Life Choice Act 2019 coming into force?''\n\nThe two options will be:<ref name=\"referendum info\"/>\n*''Yes, I support the End of Life Choice Act 2019 coming into force.''\n*''No, I do not support the End of Life Choice Act 2019 coming into force.''\n\n== Public opinion ==\nA poll in July 2019 found that 72% of the public supported some kind of assisted dying for the terminally ill.\nSupport over the past 20 years has averaged around 68%.<ref name=\"NZH pass\"/> During the 16-month-long select committee stage of the End of Life Choice Bill, 39,000 public submissions were made, with 90% of submitters opposed to it.<ref name=\"Stuff pass\"/> Over one thousand doctors signed an open letter saying that they \"want no part in assisted suicide\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Collins |first1=Simon |title=1000 Kiwi doctors sign letter against euthanasia |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12242957 |accessdate=29 January 2020 |work=The New Zealand Herald |date=22 June 2019 |language=en-NZ}}</ref>\n\n{| class= \"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;line-height:14px;text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"height:35px\"\n!scope=\"column\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"min-width:50px;\"|Date\n!scope=\"column\" rowspan=\"2\"|Polling organisation\n!scope=\"column\" rowspan=\"2\"|Sample size\n!scope=\"column\" style=\"width:60px\"|For\n!scope=\"column\" style=\"width:60px\"|Against\n!scope=\"column\" style=\"width:60px\"|Undecided\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Lead\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background:green; width:60px;\"|\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background:red; width:60px;\"|\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background:gray; width:60px;\"|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2020-02-12\"|'''8\u201312 Feb 2020'''\n| [https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/support-legalising-euthanasia-dips-but-majority-still-in-favour-poll 1 News Colmar Brunton]\n| 1,004 || style=\"background:lightgreen\" |'''65''' || 25 || 9 || style=\"background:green; color:white;\"|'''40'''\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2019-11-17\"|'''17\u201326 Nov 2019'''\n| [http://www.voxy.co.nz/politics/5/355896 Horizon Research]\n| 1,521 || style=\"background:lightgreen\" |'''70''' || 30 || \u2013 || style=\"background:green; color:white;\"|'''40'''\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"2019-07-24\"|'''20\u201324 Jul 2019'''\n| [https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/strong-support-legalising-euthanasia-in-1-news-colmar-brunton-poll-mps-set-thrash-details 1 News Colmar Brunton]\n| 1,003 || style=\"background:lightgreen\" |'''72''' || 20 || 7 || style=\"background:green; color:white